description:
Each instance of the `data` object (child of the `dataset` object) represents a set of data which is to be plotted on the chart and determines a set of data which would appear on the chart. For a box and whisker chart, one instance of the `data` object looks like this: 

<pre class="language-javascript"><code>
"dataset"[{
	"seriesname": "Previous Year",
	"data": [{
		"value": "2400,2000,2500,2800,3500,4000, 3700, 3750, 3880, 5000,5500,7500,8000,8200, 8400, 8500, 8550, 8800, 8700, 9000, 14000",
		}]
	}]
</code></pre>
